				<outline text="I’ve come back to thinking I want a reMarkable (or similar) tablet again. I love paper notebooks to flick back through for some information but once I move to a new book this is impossible. Also like the idea of annotating/note taking from a book at the same time. Have to actually research how good it really is first. Seems Supernote might be better. Will take this research line over to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://fondoftea.com/#e-Ink%20Tablets&quot;&gt;wiki&lt;/a&gt;." created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 15:31:09 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Whilst looking up the name of the next &lt;i&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Stormlight_Archive&quot;&gt;Stormlight Archives&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt; book to read, I found out about another epic fantasy series, &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robin_Hobb#The_Realm_of_the_Elderlings&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;Realm of the Elderlings&lt;/i&gt; by Robin Hodd&lt;/a&gt;." created="Mon, 25 Oct 2021 15:14:08 GMT" type="outline"/>
